maven phases run in order
validate → compile → test → package → verify → install → deploy
mvn clean - deletes the target/ directory. removes old compiled files and artifacts
mvn compile - compiles java source code from src/main/java to check if source code compiles successfully generate .class files in target directory
mvn test - compiles test classes and runs unit test from src/test/java
mvn package - compiles code, runs test and packages the app to jar or war target. o/p target/myapp.jar
mvn install - installs the artifact into local Maven repository so other local projects can use this artifact
mvn deploy - build the project and upload the artifact to remote repository (nexus / artifactory)
mvn validate - checks project structure and validate pom.xml is correct
mvn verify - runs integration tests and performs quality checks (tests how multiple components work together using real dependencies)

mvn clean        # remove old build
mvn compile      # compile source
mvn test         # run tests
mvn package      # create jar
mvn install      # save jar locally
mvn deploy       # publish jar

mvn clean package - removes the old build and creates a new build in the target directory.
mvn clean install - removes the old build and creates a new build and upload to local maven repository

arguments (-D properties)
-DskipTests → compiles tests, doesn’t run them
-Dmaven.test.skip=true → skips compiling tests also

mvn profiles - profiles allow environment‑specific builds.
example pom.xml profile
<profiles>
  <profile>
    <id>dev</id>
  </profile>
  <profile>
    <id>prod</id>
  </profile>
</profiles>
mvn clean install -Pdev
mvn clean install -Pprod
mvn clean install -Pdev,qa - activate multiple profiles

-o	Offline mode -	mvn -o clean install
-s	Custom settings.xml	- mvn -s settings.xml clean install - changes how Maven connects to repositories (URLs, credentials, proxies, mirrors), not how the project is built
-Dmaven.repo.local	Custom local repo	- mvn clean install -Dmaven.repo.local=/tmp/m2

plugin specific arguments also there
mvn test -Dtest=MyTest
mvn verify -Dit.test=ITTest
mvn clean compile -Dmaven.compiler.source=17 -Dmaven.compiler.target=17

mvn clean install -U (Update Snapshots) - Forces Maven to re‑download SNAPSHOT dependencies from remote repositories. Ignores cached versions in local repo

